== Ongoing and Planned Trials
<sec:trials-ongoing>

The ME/CFS clinical trial landscape has expanded significantly since 2020, partly driven by overlap with long COVID research. Key ongoing or recently initiated trials include:
  // TODO: needs #table() wrapper
[- *LIFT Trial* (Brigham], [Women's Hospital): LDN combined with pyridostigmine for ME/CFS. Double-blind RCT],
    - *UAB LDN dose-finding* (University of Alabama, Younger lab): Establishing optimal LDN dosing for ME/CFS
    - *Nacul LDN RCT* (UBC / BC Women's Hospital): Double-blind RCT of LDN for ME/CFS
    - *Lumbrokinase trial* (Mount Sinai): Fibrinolytic agent targeting microclots in ME/CFS and long COVID
    - *Rapamycin trial* (multi-site, US): mTOR inhibition for immune and metabolic modulation
    - *CHIIME* (UCSF / PolyBio Research Foundation): Investigating viral tissue persistence in ME/CFS and long COVID
    - *Masitinib* (AB Science): Mast cell inhibitor in phase II for ME/CFS with MCAS features
    - *tVNS multi-site trial*: Transcutaneous vagus nerve stimulation for autonomic and immune modulation
    - *Wearable pacing study* (Scripps Research): Validating wearable-guided pacing protocols
Patients seeking to participate in clinical trials can search ClinicalTrials.gov (filtering by “myalgic encephalomyelitis” or “chronic fatigue syndrome”), contact national ME/CFS organizations for trial registries, or consult the research registry in Appendix @app:research-registry.

